    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-09T19:57:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-09T19:57:00-05:00" n="473"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/5–954: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d473fn1">Drafted by the Secretary of State.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-09T20:57:00-04:00"
                            >May 9, 1954—8:57 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 49. For Under Secretary from Secretary.
                    You are authorized to support in general terms French initiative looking toward
                    an armistice agreement incorporating effective and adequate safeguards and under
                    international supervision. You should throw in additional language reiterating
                    established <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> policy concerning objective of
                    assuring independence and freedom of Associated States. In so far as relates to
                    a guarantee you should make clear that the US must reserve its position until it
                    is known more clearly what would be the nature of the settlement to be
                    guaranteed and the obligations of the guarantors.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
